  "prompt": "What is the condition of alcohol ban in Bihar?",
  "response": "As of the latest update, Bihar maintains a stringent prohibition on the sale and consumption of alcohol. This law was enacted in April 2016 under the leadership of Chief Minister Nitish Kumar, aiming to improve public health and social conditions by reducing alcohol-related issues such as domestic violence and health disorders.\n\nThe prohibition extends to all types of liquor, including Indian-made foreign liquor (IMFL), country-made liquor, and even locally brewed beverages. There are strict penalties in place for violations, with fines and possible imprisonment for those caught manufacturing, selling, transporting, or consuming alcohol.\n\nThe enforcement of this ban includes regular checks, raids, and surveillance by law enforcement agencies. However, there have been challenges in fully implementing the prohibition, as illegal trade and black-market activities continue to pose difficulties.\n\nIt is important to check current and local regulations, as policies and enforcement can evolve.",
